column1: I am happy with my life.
I had a good day.
What should I do about this?
I received a troubling message today.
I am scared about the future.
I am going to meet my birth parents tomorrow.
I am worried that I'm not enough.
I am worried that I'll never be enough.
I had a hard day at work.
I used to have suicidal thoughts.
I used to think about hurting myself.
I used to think about killing myself.
I'm struggling right now and just need to talk to someone.
I don't want to die, but I don't know how to live.
Not physically tired, but emotionally.
I'm so tired of this.
I can't keep doing this.
I just want to be alone.
Everyone hates me.
I hate people.
I don't have anyone that cares for me.
No one ever thinks about me.
I don't want to be a bother.
You don't have to worry about me, I'm good.
Why does this keep happening to me?
I wish I was never born.
I don't want to wake up tomorrow.
I want to die.
I want to hurt myself.
I want to kill myself.
I want to kill myself with a gun.
I am afraid that I might hurt myself.
I've had thoughts about hurting myself.
I've had thought about killing myself.
I am planning to end my life.
This nightmare will only be over when I die.
I wish I did not exist.
If anything happens to me, promise to take care of mom.
I want to disappear.
I'm gonna do it!
I need something to dull the pain.
